Class FashionService.SearchFilter

  • java.lang.Object
    • tech.aiq.fashion.api.FashionService.SearchFilter
  • Enclosing class:
    FashionService

    public static final class FashionService.SearchFilter
extends java.lang.Object
    The match filter class. The filter class allows user to manipulate the filter setting without need to understand the logic and dependency among the different kind of filters.

      • isColorFilter

        public boolean isColorFilter(java.lang.String filter_name)
        check if the filter is for color Due to support for internal translation, the color filter name is dynamic. Pls use this function to check if application want to display the actual color also.
        Parameters:
        filter_name - filter type to check. not null.
        Returns:
        true if the filter is for color. false otherwise

      • isFilterAffectOthers

        public boolean isFilterAffectOthers(java.lang.String filter_name)
        check if a filter's change will affect other filters when a filter affects other filters and the value of that filter is changed, it is necessary to reread all of the filters and their settings from the SearchFilter object again if further operation is needed.
        Parameters:
        filter_name - filter type to check. not null.
        Returns:
        true if the change in the filter potentially affects other filters. false otherwise

      • isFilterValueUnique

        public boolean isFilterValueUnique(java.lang.String filter_name)
        check if a filter's value must be a single value (ie, must have a value and can only have one value) some filters are the dependency of other filters, so it is required to be there so the rest of the filters are makeing sense.
        Parameters:
        filter_name - filter type to check. not null.
        Returns:
        true if the filter requires a single value

      • setFilterValues

        public void setFilterValues(@NonNull
                            java.lang.String filter_name,
                            @NonNull
                            java.util.List<java.lang.String> values)
        Set new active filter values for a filter.
        Parameters:
        filter_name - filter type of the new active values. not null.
        values - a list of filter values to apply to this filter, not null. if need to remove the filter, just set it to empty.

      • setMaxPrice

        public void setMaxPrice(double max_price)
        set the the maximum price in the location's currency. this will filter out products with higher price.
        Parameters:
        max_price - the new maximum price. Pls note that if the value is over system limit or smaller than the minimal price, it will be ignored.

      • setMinPrice

        public void setMinPrice(double min_price)
        set the the minimal price in the location's currency. this will filter out products with lowwer price.
        Parameters:
        min_price - the new minimum price. Pls note that if the value is negative or larger than the maximum price, it will be ignored.
